3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates PEPE/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The exchange applies a base funding rate of 0.01% when the premium is within ±0.05%, with adjustments based on market conditions. Copy traders following popular strategies can create sudden demand imbalances, leading to elevated funding rates during trending periods. Bitget caps funding rates at ±2% per interval to prevent extreme scenarios."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","PEPE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PEPE/USDT funding rates on Bitget frequently deviate from other exchanges due to the platform's retail-heavy user base and copy trading features that amplify momentum trades. The pair's high volatility and speculative nature create significant funding rate premiums during bull runs, often exceeding 0.1% per 8-hour period. Bitget's fast listing of new meme coins and aggressive marketing to retail traders makes PEPE funding rates particularly responsive to social media sentiment."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PEPE/USDT funding rates on Bitget have shown extreme volatility patterns, ranging from -0.5% to +1.8% during major price movements in 2023-2024. The highest positive rates typically occur during weekend periods when copy trading activity peaks and institutional arbitrageurs reduce operations. Negative funding rates are less common but can persist during broad crypto market downturns when long liquidations cascade. Monthly average funding rates have ranged from 0.02% to 0.35%, significantly higher than Bitcoin or Ethereum pairs due to speculative positioning."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between Bitget and tier-1 exchanges like Binance or OKX frequently yields 0.05-0.2% spreads during high volatility periods. Bitget's copy trading ecosystem creates predictable funding rate spikes when popular traders open large PEPE positions, offering systematic arbitrage entry points. The exchange's relatively lower liquidity compared to major competitors means funding rates can remain elevated for multiple intervals before correcting. Calendar arbitrage opportunities emerge around Bitget's promotional events and copy trader competitions when PEPE trading volume surges."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PEPE's extreme price volatility can quickly erode funding rate profits through adverse price movements, especially given the token's susceptibility to 30-50% daily swings. Bitget's newer market presence means potential counterparty risks and the possibility of trading halts during extreme market conditions. Copy trading cascades can create sudden liquidity gaps, leading to poor execution prices when entering or exiting arbitrage positions. The meme coin's lack of fundamental value drivers makes technical analysis less reliable, increasing the difficulty of timing funding rate arbitrage entries and exits."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Bitget charge funding fees for PEPE/USDT perpetuals?","answer":"Bitget charges PEPE/USDT funding fees every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. This tri-daily schedule allows for more frequent arbitrage opportunities compared to exchanges with daily funding."},{"question":"Why are PEPE funding rates higher on Bitget than other exchanges?","answer":"Bitget's retail-focused user base and copy trading features create stronger directional bias in PEPE positioning. When popular copy traders go long, their followers amplify the demand, driving funding rates higher than institutional-heavy exchanges."},{"question":"What's the maximum funding rate Bitget can charge on PEPE/USDT?","answer":"Bitget caps funding rates at ±2% per 8-hour interval for all perpetual contracts including PEPE/USDT. However, rates typically stay well below this threshold, with extreme readings around ±0.5% during major market moves."},{"question":"How does copy trading affect PEPE funding rate arbitrage on Bitget?","answer":"Copy trading creates predictable funding rate patterns when influential traders open large PEPE positions, as followers automatically replicate trades. This provides systematic arbitrage opportunities but also increases position correlation risk during market stress."}]}]
